WEBVTT

00:02.368 --> 00:05.012
Please, have a seat, Mr. Morgan.

00:05.368 --> 00:07.007
Do you mind if I call you John?

00:07.591 --> 00:08.633
Johnny.

00:09.293 --> 00:11.612
And how did you come
to find me, Johnny?

00:11.900 --> 00:14.052
I saw your ad in one
of those m-magazines

00:14.194 --> 00:16.448
they have in the mail,
the <i>Penny Saver.</i>

00:16.587 --> 00:19.349
You probably saw
my smoking cessation ad.

00:19.461 --> 00:21.670
"Guaranteed results
or your money back"?

00:21.787 --> 00:23.250
I don't smoke.

00:23.348 --> 00:25.040
Well, you certainly don't look

00:25.173 --> 00:26.936
like you need
to lose any weight.

00:27.125 --> 00:29.132
Your ad said something about...

00:29.436 --> 00:31.124
curbing compulsions.

00:31.230 --> 00:32.283
Absolutely.

00:32.396 --> 00:34.650
I've found posthypnotic
suggestion to be

00:34.773 --> 00:38.371
one of the most powerful weapons
in a therapist's arsenal.

00:38.471 --> 00:41.231
I want to stop.
I really do.

00:41.332 --> 00:45.135
If I have to go on medication,
whatever, I'm willing to try.

00:45.250 --> 00:47.980
Tell me about the behavior
you want to curtail.

00:48.097 --> 00:50.582
- Start from the beginning.
- I always, uh,

00:50.781 --> 00:53.848
had these impulses,
you know, even as a kid.

00:53.952 --> 00:55.417
The first time I tried it,

00:55.537 --> 00:56.958
it was scary.

00:57.361 --> 00:58.822
But it felt amazing.

00:58.929 --> 01:00.669
My whole body came alive.

01:00.795 --> 01:03.009
When my foster family
saw the evidence...

01:03.506 --> 01:04.583
they kicked me out.

01:04.703 --> 01:05.991
I bounced from house to house

01:06.122 --> 01:08.294
until I learned how to hide it.

01:08.422 --> 01:11.182
It's a shame so many people
have such a negative reaction

01:11.318 --> 01:13.098
to something so natural.

01:13.360 --> 01:15.625
Was that the first time
you touched yourself?

01:15.763 --> 01:17.063
No.

01:17.475 --> 01:19.344
I skinned a cat.

01:20.518 --> 01:23.103
- It was already dead.
- So...

01:23.385 --> 01:25.935
you went around
finding dead animals?

01:26.071 --> 01:28.051
Yeah. First couple of times.

01:28.157 --> 01:32.616
Then I learned that killing them
was just as good.

01:32.735 --> 01:34.145
Even better.

01:34.936 --> 01:37.327
And this compulsion followed you

01:37.451 --> 01:38.915
into your adult life?

01:39.040 --> 01:40.965
No. I don't harm
animals anymore.

01:41.095 --> 01:43.596
I haven't since
I was a teenager.

01:43.709 --> 01:45.890
Did you know that
killing animals

01:46.020 --> 01:48.867
is a predictor for psychopaths?

01:49.005 --> 01:50.235
I learned that in prison.

01:50.332 --> 01:51.673
Armed robbery.

01:51.791 --> 01:53.439
But it got me thinking.

01:53.583 --> 01:56.869
What made me... the way I am?

01:56.976 --> 01:59.106
Who were my <i>real</i> parents?

01:59.234 --> 02:01.558
Well, they had a computer at the
joint, and I didn't have nothing

02:01.694 --> 02:03.744
- but time, so...
- Mr. Morgan, you know,

02:03.877 --> 02:06.032
I-I may not be qualified
to help you.

02:06.166 --> 02:08.354
No, you <i>have</i> to help, Doctor.

02:08.473 --> 02:11.203
I don't know what to do,
because those thoughts...

02:11.356 --> 02:12.711
haven't stopped.

02:12.832 --> 02:13.514
If anything,

02:13.657 --> 02:15.517
they've gotten harder to ignore

02:15.638 --> 02:17.853
since I found out who I am.

02:18.313 --> 02:20.887
And what do those thoughts
tell you to do?

02:21.008 --> 02:22.985
They told me to
retrace my roots,

02:23.107 --> 02:25.759
so I'm renting the house
where my father lived.

02:26.137 --> 02:28.639
They also told me to hurt women.

02:29.428 --> 02:31.361
But not just hurt them.

02:32.117 --> 02:33.584
Skin them.

02:34.103 --> 02:35.492
Like the cats.

02:37.062 --> 02:38.523
Stop moving!

02:40.432 --> 02:41.385
Shut up!

02:41.509 --> 02:44.065
This is delicate work.

02:44.582 --> 02:47.246
I didn't have the same skills
as my father.

02:47.341 --> 02:48.977
I didn't get the
medical training.

02:49.096 --> 02:50.755
I made a mess.

02:52.698 --> 02:54.177
You think it's too late?

02:54.291 --> 02:56.402
It's never too late
to turn yourself in.

02:56.539 --> 02:58.210
No, to go to medical school.

02:58.323 --> 03:00.040
I'll never live up to him.

03:00.159 --> 03:02.171
That's why I wanted to stop.

03:03.298 --> 03:04.389
You see,

03:04.502 --> 03:07.213
my name isn't Morgan.

03:07.381 --> 03:09.251
It's Thredson.

03:10.639 --> 03:12.618
I'm the son of Bloody Face.

